README: epackage.el for Emacs
-----------------------------

Description

	An Emacs extension for Distributed Emacs Lisp Package System
	(DELPS). With it, you can install Emacs extensions that have
	been put available as git DVCS repositories. This format is
	called "epackage". The details of epackaging are described in
	the commentary of epackage.el.

Important files

    	COPYING		GPL-2+ Licence
    	INSTALL         Install instructions
    	ChangeLog	Project change records

Project details

	Homepage	http://freshmeat.net/projects/emacs-epackage
	Bugs		See freshmeat page
	Source code	See freshmeat page

	Depends
	- Emacs 22.1+ (released 2007).
	- git[1], any version.
	- Depends only on standard Emacs. Does not use external or
          "cl" libraries.

References

	[1] Git Distributed Version Control System (DVCS).
	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git_(software)

